<TITLE> 10 hurt in BCL clashes at Barisal Polytech </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  "Steps will be taken against those responsible after calling an academic council meeting," said acting principal Mir Mosharraf. The clash that lasted half an hour ensued between one faction led by the institute's BCL president Abdur Razzaque and another by its general secretary Mizanur Rahman. The injuredfive from each groupwere treated locally. The clashes erupted between the two groups over control of the campus, Nuruzzaman Chowdhury, officer in charge of Kotwali Model Police Station, told bdnews24.com. The two faction leaders traded blame over the incident. Mizan and with his supporters attacked first, said Razzaque. Mizan said 'outsiders' under Razzaque's orders attacked without provocation. Barisal city's Chhatra League convenor Ziaur Rahman Zia put the clashes down to "misunderstandings". bdn
